    "steps": [
      {
        "step_no": 1,
        "text": "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Line a large rimmed baking sheet with parchment or lightly oil it to prevent sticking.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Toss prepared sweet potato, carrots, parsnips and red onion with half the olive oil, half the minced garlic, half the lemon juice, rosemary, thyme, smoked paprika, and about two-thirds of the salt and pepper in a large bowl until evenly coated.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Spread the root vegetables in a single layer on one side of the prepared baking sheet. Roast in the preheated oven for 25 minutes, stirring or turning once halfway through to promote even browning.",
        "time_min": 25
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "While vegetables start roasting, pat salmon fillets dry and season both sides with remaining salt, pepper, and a light sprinkle of smoked paprika. Drizzle remaining olive oil over fillets and rub gently to coat.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "After the vegetables have roasted for the initial time and are beginning to soften and brown, move them slightly to make room and place salmon fillets skin-side down on the baking sheet. Return to oven and roast everything together until salmon reaches desired doneness (opaque and flakes easily), about 8–10 minutes depending on thickness.",
        "time_min": 10
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Remove the baking sheet from the oven. Squeeze remaining lemon juice over salmon and vegetables, scatter parsley and lemon zest over the top, and let rest for 2 minutes before serving.",
        "time_min": 0
      }
